TITLE: FEC presses George Santos campaign after it lists treasurer who denies taking the job
SUMMARY: Attorney Derek Ross, who disputed the Santos campaign's filing, told CNBC he has not tried to contact the campaign because it "seems like a waste of time."

TITLE: House Republicans pass bill to limit drawdowns on Strategic Petroleum Reserve
SUMMARY: The Strategic Production Response Act requires agencies to lease federal land for oil and gas drilling to offset drawdowns. It's unlikely to become law.

TITLE: Three arrested in plot linked to Iran to assassinate U.S. journalist, DOJ says
SUMMARY: A journalist in Brooklyn, New York, was the target of a murder plot directed by individuals in Iran, Attorney General Merrick Garland said.

TITLE: Former Covid chief Jeff Zients to replace Ron Klain as White House chief of staff, Biden confirms
SUMMARY: Zients is a longtime ally of both Biden and Klain and has a reputation of getting things done.

TITLE: California State Bar moves to pull Trump ally John Eastman's license over 2020 election plot
SUMMARY: Eastman's counts are related to his alleged scheme to overturn former President Donald Trump's loss to President Joe Biden in the 2020 election.

TITLE: Biden touts job growth and slowing inflation rates in speech on economy
SUMMARY: Biden spent much of the second half of 2022 asking Americans to bear with him through historically high gas prices and inflation.

TITLE: Democratic Rep. Adam Schiff launches bid for Sen. Dianne Feinstein's California seat
SUMMARY: Schiff led the House Intelligence Committee and served as lead impeachment manager for the Senate in its first trial of former President Donald Trump.

TITLE: Russian paramilitary firm Wagner Group sanctioned by U.S. for alleged ongoing criminal activity
SUMMARY: Last week, National Security Council spokesman John Kirby said U.S. intelligence estimates the Wagner Group has at least 50,000 personnel in Ukraine.

TITLE: Biden administration rolls out a blueprint for a 'renters bill of rights' – Here's what it includes
SUMMARY: The Biden administration rolled out a blueprint for a renters bill of rights, a major win for tenants, advocates say.

TITLE: U.S. will send Abrams tanks to Ukraine ahead of expected Russian offensive
SUMMARY: The 31 M1A1 Abrams sent by the Biden administration are not expected to arrive in Ukraine for several months.

TITLE: Fed's Lael Brainard among leading contenders for top White House economic post
SUMMARY: The central bank official is considered a strong candidate to succeed Brian Deece as director of the National Economic Council, the Washington Post reported.

TITLE: Former Trump UN ambassador Nikki Haley gears up for likely 2024 run for president
SUMMARY: Nikki Haley, who was former President Donald Trump's ambassador to the United Nations, is gearing up for a likely 2024 run for president against her old boss.

TITLE: Arizona Senate hopeful Ruben Gallego posts record-breaking fundraising haul in bid for Kyrsten Sinema's seat
SUMMARY: More than 27,000 donations contributed to Gallego's haul, breaking a state record previously held by incumbent Democrat Sen. Mark Kelly, the campaign said.

TITLE: Trump drops second legal challenge to New York attorney general after sanctions in Hillary Clinton case
SUMMARY: Donald Trump was sanctioned nearly $1 million for what a judge called a frivolous lawsuit against Hillary Clinton.

TITLE: Treasury tells Congress it will suspend some federal retirement investments after debt limit breach
SUMMARY: The Treasury Department will suspend funding for a federal employee retirement benefit program until the debt ceiling is raised or suspended.

TITLE: Georgia DA investigating Trump for 2020 election interference says charging 'decisions are imminent' after grand jury report
SUMMARY: Donald Trump is under investigation for possible crimes related to trying to overturn his 2020 election loss to President Joe Biden.

TITLE: Classified documents found at Mike Pence's Indiana home
SUMMARY: The classified documents were discovered on Jan. 16 after Pence had outside counsel search his own home and records "out of an abundance of caution."

TITLE: Putin's nuclear threats move Doomsday Clock closest ever to Armageddon, atomic scientists say
SUMMARY: The 2023 countdown time on the clock is "90 seconds to midnight," 10 seconds closer to "doomsday" than it had been set at last year.

TITLE: The FDA's power to approve drugs faces sweeping challenge in lawsuit seeking to pull abortion pill from U.S. market
SUMMARY: If the lawsuit prevails, women across the U.S. would lose access to the most common abortion method. The FDA's powers to approve drugs would also be weakened.

TITLE: Former top FBI counterintelligence agent Charles McGonigal charged with violating Russia sanctions
SUMMARY: Charles McGonigal, a former FBI agent for counterintelligence, faces charges related to services provided to Russian oligarch Oleg Deripaska.

TITLE: Rep. Ruben Gallego launches bid for Sen. Kyrsten Sinema's Arizona seat
SUMMARY: The announcement makes Gallego the first candidate in what could be a three-way race for Sinema's Arizona Senate seat.

TITLE: M&M's pulls 'spokescandies' amid right-wing outrage, before Super Bowl ad starring Maya Rudolph
SUMMARY: Candy maker Mars said it is replacing its M&Ms "spokescandies" with actress Maya Rudolph after facing right-wing criticism.

TITLE: SEC fines Bloomberg $5 million for disclosure violations on fixed-income prices
SUMMARY: The SEC settled charges against financial and media company Bloomberg LP for misleading disclosures.

TITLE: GOP Rep. George Santos should resign from Congress, New York state voters say in new poll
SUMMARY: New York voters hold a strongly unfavorable opinion of Santos, who has admitted to lying about his background and faces multiple investigations.

TITLE: Jeff Zients reportedly will be Biden’s next chief of staff
SUMMARY: Jeff Zients will serve as President Joe Biden's next chief of staff, according to a report from the Washington Post Sunday.

TITLE: Biden makes surprise video appearance on 'SNL,' joining host Aubrey Plaza
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden made a surprise video appearance on "Saturday Night Live" during host Aubrey Plaza's monologue.

TITLE: Top U.S. spy agency says more security assistance from allies is crucial for Ukraine to prevail
SUMMARY: The director of America's top spy agency said Russia's war in Ukraine will require the West to continue to provide security assistance packages.

TITLE: Legislators call Biden's treatment of classified documents 'irresponsible'
SUMMARY: Most Americans think both Biden and Trump have handled classified material inappropriately, according to a poll released Sunday by ABC News.

TITLE: FBI finds more classified documents in 13-hour search of Biden home
SUMMARY: The Biden White House has been criticized for how it has handled the discovery of classified records in private locations used by Joe Biden.

TITLE: Ron Klain, Biden’s White House chief of staff, is reportedly expected to step down
SUMMARY: White House Chief of Staff Ron Klain is preparing to step down from the Biden administration in the coming weeks, The New York Times reported.
